[The German authorities have commendably managed to prevent the introduction of the ASF virus, circulating within the wild boar population in German states bordering Poland, into pig farms since its initial introduction from that country in September 2020.

For a recent report on the event in Pig Progress, please refer to https://www.pigprogress.net/Health/Articles/2021/7/ASF-Germany-first-outbreaks-of-ASF-in-domestic-pigs-771160E/. The interactive map included is expected to be updated soon, adding the locations of the 2
outbreaks in domestic pigs in Brandenburg. - Mod.AS

